The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, January 13, 2004 				 Italy pat for Buddha 
																								Calcutta, Jan. 12: Bengal is becoming more attractive as a business destination, Italian consul-general Agostino Pinna said after his meeting with chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today. 																								A delegation from Tuscany will be in the city on January 16 and 17. The team of Ambrogio Brenna, the regions minister for industry and handicraft, Mauro Ginanneschi, the director of Toscana Promozione (Economic Promotion Agency of Tuscany), Giovanni Cordoni, the president of Ceseca  Shoe Industry Service Centre  and Marta Javarone, a Promozione official, will discuss possible areas of cooperation between Italy and Bengal. 																								I had a fruitful discussion with the chief minister today. We identified several areas of cooperation, particularly leather. Another area was gems and jewellery and Bhattacharjee expressed interest in food processing and agro-business, Pinna said. 
